Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450}(lengthways into 1cm slices, no need to peel). Use a #knife or #cookie cutter{} to make a few 'starchips', then chop the rest into 1cm wide chips.

Pop your starchips and chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if you'd like, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Lay the @British chicken breasts{2} into an #ovenproof dish{}, drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if you'd like.

When the oven is hot, roast the chicken on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Pop the chips on the top shelf to roast until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, trim the @green beans{150}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30}.

== Tomato Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a medium #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the shallot and cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in half the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @tomato passata{1} and @chicken stock paste{10} to the pan and stir to combine. Bring to a boil until thickened and reduced by half, ~{4-5%minutes}. Taste and season with @pepper{} and a pinch of @?sugar{} if you'd like.

When the chicken is cooked and the sauce has thickened, pour the tomato sauce over the chicken and sprinkle with the cheese. Return to the oven to bake until the cheese has melted, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Remove from the oven once ready and cover with #foil{}. Set aside to rest for a couple of minutes.

== Garlicky Green Beans ==

Meanwhile, wipe out the frying pan and pop back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the remaining garlic, then turn the heat down to medium and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add a splash of @water{} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some foil. Cook until the beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

== To Serve ==

Share the cheesy chicken and tomato sauce between your plates.

Plate up the green beans and chips alongside, then finish with the starchips to make dinner out of this world!

Enjoy!

> Space Ranger Mission: New stars have been discovered in the galaxy! Little space rangers can help stamp out the 'starchips' with a star-shaped cookie cutter - you can even use different sized cutters to make a whole constellation.